        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:58PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Perry Park, or 29 miles south of Denver, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Castle Rock, Larkspur, Perry Park, Greenland and Shamballa.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
